OL,4,Cvictim: 'Don't go near the water'
OL,6,FLily-May Wright, who attended a
OL,7,Fceremony at the site where he drowned,
OL,8,Fsaid: ''I was just brought to my knees
OL,9,Fwhen I knew it was him. It's something
OL,10,Fwe all used to do - but now some of us
OL,11,Fwon't even go to the swimming pool now.
OL,13,F"We lost him at 16, he had his 17th
OL,14,Fbirthday coming up, he had his GCSEs
OL,15,Fcoming up, he had everything else
OL,16,Fahead of him. It just makes you think
OL,17,Fwell that could have been me. Just
OL,18,Fdon't go near the water."
