OL,6,FJamie-Lee Pemberton said: ''I'd feel
OL,7,Fconfident to use one now - it just
OL,8,Fmade me think, if there'd been one
OL,9,Fthere at the time, I could have used
OL,10,Fit and saved him.''
OL,12,FNickie Arthur, from the Lowland Rescue
OL,13,Fteam said: "To use a throwline, you
OL,14,Ffirst ring 999. Get the throwline bag,
OL,15,Fopen it and throw the line so it lands
OL,16,Fbeyond the casualty. Shout to them to
OL,17,Fget the line, not the bag. Make sure
OL,18,Fthey lie flat the opposite way, so
OL,19,Fwater isn't going in their face, and
OL,20,Fgradually pull them in.''
